##########################################
1. The first step is to get your download 
credentials to populate
$SSARAHOME/password_config.py

With this you are able to run ssara and get
the data directly from the data sources

2.  Now run the same examples that you used to
test the installation. In contrast to the testing 
ssara is downloading the data for you from the 
data centers (WinSAR, ESA, ASF).

3. As you are testing you may want to use a 
different SCRATCHDIR directory. This can be done
with the alias TESTBENCH, which sets it to $SCRATCHDIR/TESTBENCH.
There are also aliasses TESTBENCH1, TESTBENCH2, TESTBENCH3. 
After running an alias go with cd $SCRATCHDIR to 
your working directory. 

4. Try processing the different steps individually. After each step look in the different directories
to see what happened:
process_rsmas.pl $SAMPLESDIR/SinabungT495F50AlosA.template --startssara       --stopssara
process_rsmas.pl $SAMPLESDIR/SinabungT495F50AlosA.template --startprepare     --stopprepare
process_rsmas.pl $SAMPLESDIR/SinabungT495F50AlosA.template --startslc         --stopsslc
process_rsmas.pl $SAMPLESDIR/SinabungT495F50AlosA.template --startprocessfilt --stopprocessfilt
process_rsmas.pl $SAMPLESDIR/SinabungT495F50AlosA.template --startcoregist    --stopcoregist
process_rsmas.pl $SAMPLESDIR/SinabungT495F50AlosA.template --startprocessdone --stopprocessdone
process_rsmas.pl $SAMPLESDIR/SinabungT495F50AlosA.template --startpysar

5. Once you are familiar with these steps run everything at once:
process_rsmas.pl $SAMPLESDIR/SinabungT495F50AlosA.template 

6. To run other data sets create new template files by replacing the corresponding parameters.

7. All the examples in the samples directories are working and are meant to demonstrate particular processing aspects.

